Nigerian President Muhammadu Buhari has touched down in South Africa. Buhari is paying an official visit following a spate of anti-foreigner violence. JOHANNESBURG - Nigerian President Muhammadu Buhari is meeting with President Cyril Ramaphosa in Pretoria. Buhari's visit comes following the recent xenophobic attacks. WATCH: Nigerian President's visit to SA Ramaphosa said the meeting will further strengthen ties between the countries. Buhari is paying an official visit following a spate of anti-foreigner violence. Nigeria expressed concerns that its expatriates were being targeted and some even decided to flee the country.